  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the Improve SCA Bridge study is to characterize the care pathway flow of
      post‐acute myocardial infarction (MI) patients as a result of standard assessments of left
      ventricular ejection fraction (LVEF) in the acute phase (≤14 days post‐ acute MI) and chronic
      phase (≥40‐90 days post‐acute MI).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      To determine how many patients are referred for sudden cardiac death (SCD) risk
      stratification and management, indicated for implantable cardioverter defibrillator (ICD), or
      cardiac resynchronization therapy- defibrillator (CRT-D) implant, and how many receive such
      devices within 12 months of experiencing an MI.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
